race.comment: GRAND MILLESIME (9) peaks off narrow heavily-bet defeats with the latest at Kyneton over this distance. Will enjoy a drop in class and is perfectly placed to score. SUMO SANDY (2) is the threat. Just missed at Sandown-Hillside over this trip on debut and ran solid races following also in stronger. He's won both Cranbourne jumpouts in preparation for this and Meech will give him every chance from an inside barrier. I AM TITAN (1) disappointed at Wangaratta third up, but had been building nicely into that. but was heading in the right direction prior. Needs to find more but has the blinkers on again and is in the mix. CRACKERJACK HATCH (13) has more to offer third-up and maps for a soft run. She will be around the mark as well. ASHEN KNIGHT (5) debuts and has trialled well. Has an awkward gate but keep safe.
